 (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Hirschfeld1921EthioFalasiGlossary"/><citedRange unit="page"> 224</citedRange></bibl> wrongly renders Amh. <foreign xml:lang="am">ወዛ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>wazzā</quote></cit> (translation of <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/></bibl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልሕየ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>lǝḥya</quote></cit>) by ‘perspire’; it also means ‘be pretty’) <lb/>
